TNK-BP Says Internal Corruption Probe Leads to 37 Criminal Cases

-- B y   S t e p h e n   B i e r m a n
-- 
2011-09-08T11:57:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-08/tnk-bp-says-internal-corruption-probe-leads-to-37-criminal-cases.html
TNK-BP, BP Plc’s Russian venture
with a group of billionaires, disciplined 92 people as a result
of an internal corruption probe this year that has led to 37
criminal cases.  “Integrity is one of TNK-BP’s core values and as such the
company does not tolerate any form of corruption or fraud,”
Maxim Barsky, deputy chief executive officer the Moscow-based
company, said in an e-mailed statement today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stephen Bierman in Moscow 
 sbierman1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Will Kennedy  at   wkennedy3@bloomberg.net . 